.TH cerebrod 8 "May 2005" "cerebrod @VERSION@" cerebrod
.SH "NAME"
cerebrod \- cerebro monitoring daemon
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B cerebrod [OPTIONS]
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The
.B cerebrod
daemon is responsible for distributing and receiving cluster
node data from each node in the cluster for use within the
.B Cerebro
suite of tools and libraries.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B  -h, --help
Output help
.TP
.B  -v, --version
Output version
.if @MANPAGE_DEBUG@ \{
.TP
.B  -c, --config-file
Specify alternate configuration file
.TP
.B  -m, --config-module
Specify configuration module
.TP
.B  -d, --debug
Turn on debugging and run daemon in foreground
\}
.SH "CONFIGURATION FILE"
The configuration file configures the features and behavior of the
.B cerebrod 
daemon.  The configuration ultimately affects the utility of
the 
.B Cerebro
suite of tools and libraries.

The user is highly encouraged to learn about the various
configuration options, since proper configuration can help
improve the performance of
.B Cerebro
as a whole.

The default configuration file loaded by 
.B cerebrod
is @CEREBROD_CONFIG_FILE_DEFAULT@.  
.if @MANPAGE_DEBUG@ \{
An alternate configuration file
can be specified on the command line with the
.I -c 
option.
\}

Specific details of the configurable features and
configurable options can be found in the
.B cerebrod.conf(5)
manpage.  

.SH "CONFIGURATION MODULE"
A configuration module format has been developed into 
.B cerebrod
to alleviate the potential difficulty of configuring many different
cluster nodes with different configuration files.  The configuration
module loads an alternate set of default configuration options.  For
example, if the cluster contains a cluster configuration database, a
configuration module could be written to read from the cluster
configuration database, and configure each
.B cerebrod
daemon in the cluster based on the parameters stored in the database.
Therefore, a different configuration file does not have to be written
and distributed for each cluster node.

The configuration loaded by a configuration module can be overrided by
the options specified in the configuration file.

The following config modules
are distributed by
.B cerebrod:

.ie @MANPAGE_GENDERSLLNL@ \{
gendersllnl - Configures the
.B cerebrod
daemon specifically for use on LLNL clusters.

\}
.el \{
No configuration modules are searched in this build.

\}

.ie @MANPAGE_STATIC_MODULES@ \{
When a config module is not specified, the above config modules are
searched for by
.B cerebrod
in the above order.
\}
.el \{
Configuration modules are searched for in the 
.B Cerebro
package library directory, @CEREBROD_MODULE_DIR@, in the above order.
If none of the above are found, 
.B cerebrod
will search for other configuration modules.
\}

It is not necessary for a configuration module to be found and loaded.

.if @MANPAGE_DEBUG@ \{
A configuration module can also be specified on the command line with
the
.I -m 
option.
\}

.if !@MANPAGE_STATIC_MODULES@ \{
For more information on writing 
.B cerebrod
configuration modules see XXX.
\}

.SH "CLUSTERLIST MODULE"
In order for 
.B Cerebro
to be utilized at its full potential, a list of cluster nodes should be
loaded into the
.B cerebrod
daemon.  Although
.B Cerebro
can be used without a clusterlist, some features will be diminished
without one.  For example, there will be no way to determine the down
nodes of the cluster if there is no knowledge of what all of the
nodes in the cluster actually are.

The list of cluster nodes can be specified in several formats by using
one of a number of clusterlist modules.  Clusterlist modules can
be selected using the
.I clusterlist_module
configuration option in the
.B cerebrod
configuration file.
Configurable options can be passed to the clusterlist modules through the
.I clusterlist_module_options
configuration file option.  The options are typically listed as
key=value pairs.

The following config modules
are distributed by
.B cerebrod:

.if @MANPAGE_GENDERSLLNL@ \{
gendersllnl - Reads and parses a genders database with LLNL specific
attributes and values.  Can be passed a filename=value option to
specify an non-default genders database location.

\}

.if @MANPAGE_GENDERS@ \{
genders - Reads and parses a generic genders database.  Can be passed
a filename=value option to specify an non-default genders database
location.

\}

hostsfile - Reads and parses a file listing each cluster node on a
separate line.  Can be passed a filename=value option to specify an
non-default hostsfile database location.  The default hostsfile is
located at @CEREBRO_CLUSTERLIST_HOSTSFILE_DEFAULT@.

.ie @MANPAGE_STATIC_MODULES@ \{
When a clusterlist module is not specified, the above clusterlist
modules are searched for by
.B cerebrod
in the above order.
\}
.el \{
Clusterlist modules are searched for in the 
.B Cerebro
package library directory, @CEREBROD_MODULE_DIR@, in the above order.
If none of the above are found, 
.B cerebrod
will search for other clusterlist modules.
\}

It is not necessary for a configuration module to be found and loaded.
.B Cerebrod
will simply not use a clusterlist module.

.if !@MANPAGE_STATIC_MODULES@ \{
For more information on writing 
.B cerebrod
clusterlist modules see XXX.
\}

.SH "FILES"
@CEREBROD_CONFIG_FILE_DEFAULT@

@CEREBRO_CLUSTERLIST_HOSTSFILE_DEFAULT@

@CEREBRO_MODULE_DIR@
